description:
Pedro Hernandez was born (1970) in Brooklyn, New York to Puerto Rican - American parents. He's a graphic artist / illustrator / writer working in the field of freelance design.

A lifelong lover of comics, movies, books, video games, and all things technological, Pedro has sought to push the envelope with his comic universe by bringing ethnic characters to the forefront and addressing controversial topics such as; racism, corruption, and social understanding. A graduate of the School of Visual Arts, he holds a Bachelor of Fine Arts and has worked as a designer for over 20 years for such high profile companies as Sothebys, Time Magazine, The New York Times, The SyFy channel, Colgate / Palmolive, National Association Of Latino Independent Producers, USA Networks, and Lebhar-Friedman.

His original comic series COMPANY MAN is his first foray into the world of digital comics and has proven to be a ground breaking, long lasting contribution to the world of sequential art. You can see some of his artwork at www.goofeesnax.com or on FACEBOOK @ https://www.facebook.com/petehernandezIII

http://www.expertcomics.com/Blog/2013/07/pete-hernandez-iii-company-man/
name: Pete Hernandez III

description:
Raymond Mullikin is a cartoonist and credentialed educator. He teaches art classes (including Cartooning, Video Game Creation and Claymation) to children. He also creates his own children’s books, comics, computer games and animated films. His first published work was at age 12, in which designed ads (and a logo) for local businesses in his hometown. And at 16 he created his first graphic novel (The World of Weralt).

He has self-published cartoons in books, magazines, newspapers, and e-cards in the US and Canada. One of his earliest notables being “The Tumbleweed Trail” which was published in Bluemoon Comics magazine and "The World of Weralt" a fantasy graphic novel he wrote when he was 16 years old (both being in the latter 90s, while he was in high school). His animated films have been shown in film festivals throughout the world (the latest being "Miced: War of the Little Worlds", which won an award.)

He is currently working on the "Quackup" comic series as well as some children's book titles.
name: Raymond Mullikin

description:
Anthony Faella is the creator of Fatman and Fatman Comics. He is a very active creator in the Brevard County area of Florida. He has his comics for sale in Famous Faces and Funnies, and the Infinite Mushroom over in Titusville Florida. Furthermore, Anthony has been developing his comic series into a brand new tv series which has been filming locally.

Anthony states," Fatman launched in 2001, Fatman Comics provides the highest quality independent comics on the market today, including: The Fatman. Written, produced and published in Brevard County Florida, Fatman Comics strives to produce the best stories and most memorable characters found in any non-mainstream comic series today."
name: Anthony Faella

deck: Artist, writer, creator, director and journalist.
description:
Charles or better known as Charlie to his friends, is a comic artist that was heavily influenced by many of the great comic masters. Charles, work has been in many different books, he is a journalist and had talked with many key comic artist of the 20th and 21st century along with having directed a popular show that dealt with comics and artist.

He has completed several issues over the years, and has currently been linked to Space Coast Comixx.
name: Charles Apellaniz

deck: Ward Walrath Kimball was an animator for the Walt Disney Studios. He was one of Walt Disney's team of animators, known as Disney's Nine Old Men.

description:
Beth Sipps has a minor in early childhood education and a BA in Education. Since an early child she has had a strong desire to be a writer, and an editor.

Since a young teen she has had a love of horror mystery comics, her favorites are the Vault of Horror and any crime drama comic she can get her hands on. She enjoys Criminal and many other comics of that nature.
name: Beth Sipps
